s part of the review of mechanisms of coloration. This book will be essential reading for biologists studying animal coloration, but it will also be treasured by anyone curious about how birds produce and perceive their bold and brilliant color displays.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBirdsxColor. 7aNATURE / Animals / Birds.2bisacsh1 aAndersson, Staffan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuthill, Innes C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Geoffrey E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Geoffrey E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKimball, Rebecca T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcGraw, Kevin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontgomerie, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMundy, Nicholas I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrager, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrum, Richard O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThéry, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z978311044221240uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674273788?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674273788423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674273788/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK